NVIDIA GPU Health Agent
===================

GPU Health Agent provides comprehensive monitoring for NVIDIA datacenter GPUs.

Configuration
-------------

The service configuration is located at:
  /etc/default/gpuhealth

To configure the service:
  1. Edit: sudo vi /etc/default/gpuhealth
  2. Restart: sudo systemctl restart gpuhealthd

The default configuration sets log level to 'info'. Available levels:
  debug, info, warn, error, fatal, panic

Data Directory
--------------

GPU Health Agent stores data in:
  /var/lib/gpuhealth/

This directory is automatically created during installation.

Service Management
------------------

Start/stop the service:
  sudo systemctl start gpuhealthd
  sudo systemctl stop gpuhealthd

Enable/disable automatic startup:
  sudo systemctl enable gpuhealthd
  sudo systemctl disable gpuhealthd

Check service status:
  sudo systemctl status gpuhealthd

View logs:
  sudo journalctl -u gpuhealthd -f

Requirements
------------

- NVIDIA drivers version 535 or higher (recommended)
- systemd version 230 or higher
- curl

The agent will work without NVIDIA drivers but GPU monitoring will be limited.

Troubleshooting
---------------

If the service fails to start:
  1. Check logs: sudo journalctl -u gpuhealthd
  2. Verify NVIDIA drivers: nvidia-smi
  3. Check configuration: sudo vi /etc/default/gpuhealth

